We want to apply the chain rule. Set $u = \sqrt{x}-1$.

\begin{align*}
g(u) &= \sqrt{u}-1 & g'(u) &= \frac{1}{2\sqrt{u}}\\
u(x) &= \sqrt{x}-1 & u'(x) &= \frac{1}{2\sqrt{x}}\end{align*}

Combining, we get:

\begin{align*}
g'(x) &= \frac{1}{2\sqrt{x}} \cdot \frac{1}{2\sqrt{\sqrt{x}-1}}\\
&= \frac{1}{4\sqrt{x}\cdot\sqrt{\sqrt{x}-1}}\\
&= \frac{1}{4\sqrt{x \left(\sqrt{x}-1\right)}}\end{align*}
